  Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM) is a disease with different etiological, morphological, functional, clinical and therapeutic aspects. Recent investigations indicate that HCM is considerably widespread in the population (1:500). The causes seem to generate from familial or sporadic abnormalities (mutations). Depending on the clinical aspect, the complaints, and on the basis of morphologic and hemodynamic investigational results, we mainly have to consider two types of medical and surgical management.  
